nl.tue.ddss.convert.rdf2ifc

Class StreamIfcWriter

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.tue.ddss.convert.rdf2ifc.Rdf2IfcConverter
      • nl.tue.ddss.convert.rdf2ifc.StreamIfcWriter

  • public class StreamIfcWriter
extends Rdf2IfcConverter
    Author:
    Chi The class used to read IFC RDF files and write IFC SPF files. It is based on the Stream RDF library in Jena Riot to read IFC RDF files and orders elements in IFC SPF files according to triple orders in IFC RDF files.

      • StreamIfcWriter

        public StreamIfcWriter(IfcVersion version,
                       boolean updns)
        Constructor
        Parameters:
        version - IFC version for the conversion process
        updns - Set whether to update namespace for the ifcOWL ontology. Defaut value is false. If it is true, the converter will look up the namespace from the corresponding ifcOWL file in the resources folder and use it. Therefore the corresponding ifcOWL file must be updated before, otherwise it will still use the old namespace.
